HyperText Markup Language is made up of:
	•	Text content - what you see
	•	Markup - what it looks like
	•	Reference to other documents - e.g. images + videos
    •	Links to other pages
    
HTML Markup is made up of components named Tags
 
	•	Example - < NAME > Contents </NAME>
	◦	The first tag is the "opening tag"
	◦	The tag with a slash is the "closing tag"
	◦	This entire phrase is an "element"
 
 
HTML Attributes
	•	Example - <TAG ATTR="value"> Contents </TAG>
 
Italics
	•	<em>HTML is<b>reasonably straightforward</b></em>
 
Making Links
	•	Example - This website is <a href="https://www.udacity.com">my favorite</a>
 
